===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The effect of being [[shadow]]ed (in the sense of blocked), as from a [[light source]] or [[radio]] transmission.
# [[speech|Speech]] shadowing is when an individual repeats speech as they hear it immediately without delay (usually through [[earphones]]).
# {{context|espionage|lang=en}} [[secretly|Secretly]] or discreetly [[track]]ing or [[follow]]ing someone, keeping under [[surveillance]].
# A [[faint]] [[representation]]; an [[adumbration]].
#: ''There are {{...}} in savage theology '''shadowings''', quaint or majestic, of the conception of a Supreme Deity.'' &mdash; Tylor.
# {{context|computing|lang=en}} The technique of [[copy]]ing [[ROM]] contents to [[RAM]] to allow for shorter access times. The ROM chip is then disabled while the initialized [[memory]] [[location]]s are switched in on the same [[block]] of [[address]]es.
# {{context|education|lang=en}} A work experience option where students learn about a job by walking through the work day as a shadow to a competent worker.
